YEE AH SHIM on Behalf of Yee On Fok, Appellant, v. Luther WEEDIN, Commissioner of Immigration for the Port of Seattle, Wash., Appellee. No. 6465. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 11, 1931.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges, and NETERER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to motion of counsel for appellee, ordered appeal dismissed for failure of appellant to file record and docket cause; mandate forthwith.
